# Roadmap #30 — `type` is a first-class value.
# A value's type is reached with `.type`, and types compare by identity with `==`.

x := i32 5

same  := x.type == i32     # true: x was built as an i32
cross := x.type == f64     # false: i32 is not f64
meta  := i32.type == type  # true: a type's own type is the `type` root

same and meta and not (cross)
